Interface TemporalValue

All Known Implementing Classes:
TimexValue
public interface TemporalValue

Represents a temporal value, abstracted from its particular realization in text. This is placeholder which may be elaborated in the future. Implementations are strongly urged to be immutable. Implementations are only required to implement #hashCode() and #equals(Object) in terms of the structure of that sort of temporal value and are not required to attempt to determine which descriptions refer to equivalent real-world values.
